This paper primarily focuses on using ambient RF signals for human presence detection, which falls under the category of wireless networking and communication (cs.NI). The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques for processing and analyzing the RF signals, which makes it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper addresses several challenges in passive RF sensing, which involves system design and control (cs.SY) and signal processing (cs.MM).
